@gegelsmr2 I like where your head’s at though, def a Bitcoiner perspective!

I have friends/family who don’t want kids bc they think “why would I want a kid when the world has so much despair/problems”.

On the other hand, Bitcoiners think “I can give my kid such a better life than I had”🧡

@gegelsmr2 100% agree w/ resources. Still, a kid learns best through a parent’s attention &amp; more kids stretches that thin.

10 kids 100 yrs ago bc 1/2 died &amp; other 1/2 put to work 🤣 even kings rarely had more than 3 😜

10 works if you commit. It’s harder work than most think to do right.

@gegelsmr2 Start with 1 &amp; do what 99% of other parents don’t/can’t do: 

focus most of your time &amp; attention to making sure they maximize their potential - meaning minimal daycare &amp; screen time for the first 2-3 yrs min.

Believe me, when you do that … 10 won’t be the number you want 🤣😜

